INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_hnl4300','letter','1789-07-01','Stratford','','US','Henry','Lee','','George','Washington','','individual','','Although the exalted station, which your love of us and our love of you has placed you in, calls for change in mode of address, yet I cannot so quickly relinquish the old manner.','ltr_hnl4300.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_hnl4301','letter','1794-09-03','Norfolk','','US','Henry','Lee','','George','Washington','','individual','','My grief for the necessity of pointing the bayonet against the breasts of our countrymen, is equalled only by my conviction of the wisdom of your decision to compel immediate submission to the authority of the laws','ltr_hnl4301.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_hnl4302','letter','1786-10-11','New York','NY','US','Henry','Lee','','George','Washington','','individual','','The Eastern States consider a commercial connection with Spain as the only remedy for the distresses which oppress their citizens ; most of which, they say, flow from the decay of their commerce.','ltr_hnl4302.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_hnl4303','letter','1786-02-16','New York','NY','US','Henry','Lee','','George','Washington','','individual','','It is very doubtful, how our Commissioners may succeed with the Indians. We have too much reason to fear a war, which, among other evils, will increase our finance embarrassments.','ltr_hnl4303.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_hnl4304','letter','1786-08-07','New York','NY','US','Henry','Lee','','George','Washington','','individual','','My mind has no doubt of the extensive good consequences that would result to the Union from a commercial connection with Spain','ltr_hnl4304.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
